{"id":"gotcha-example-001","type":"gotcha","fact":"Example: Truthy check on numeric values fails for explicit zero - if (value) is false when value === 0.","recommendation":"Use !== undefined or !== null instead of truthy checks when the value could legitimately be 0 or empty string.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"coderabbit","reference":"PR review","date":"2026-01-09"}],"tags":["javascript","type-coercion","validation"],"affectedFiles":["**/*.ts"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-01-09T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-01-09T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-strategy-from-file-drops-filter","type":"gotcha","fact":"strategy new --from-file silently drops an embedded filter block and resets activation_mode to every_bar. The strategy wakes the LLM on every candle, bypassing warmup — can blow through token budgets (2M+ tokens observed). Filters must be installed via xvn strategy set-filter; from-file is not a valid path to set them.","recommendation":"After strategy new --from-file, always run xvn strategy show <id> to verify activation_mode and filter. If the strategy should have a filter, install it with set-filter after creation.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"operator","reference":"PR comment 2026-06-08","date":"2026-06-08"}],"tags":["xvision-cli","strategy","filter","from-file","activation-mode"],"affectedFiles":["crates/xvision-cli/src/commands/strategy.rs"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-06-08T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-06-08T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-set-filter-resets-risk","type":"gotcha","fact":"xvn strategy set-filter silently resets risk.risk_pct_per_trade to the balanced-preset default (0.015), discarding any custom risk value set via from-file or direct edit. Combined with set-filter being a no-op when a filter already exists, there is no clean CLI sequence to have both a custom risk AND a filter.","recommendation":"After set-filter, always verify risk settings with xvn strategy show <id>. If risk was customized, re-apply it after the filter is set. Track this as a known limitation until a strategy set-risk verb is added.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"operator","reference":"PR comment 2026-06-08","date":"2026-06-08"}],"tags":["xvision-cli","strategy","filter","risk","set-filter"],"affectedFiles":["crates/xvision-cli/src/commands/strategy.rs"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-06-08T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-06-08T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-rvol-tod-warmup-per-slot","type":"gotcha","fact":"rvol_tod_N requires N complete trading sessions at the same minute-slot, not just N bars. For 15m cadence: required = N × 96 bars/day (e.g. rvol_tod_20 = 1920 bars minimum). The standard warmup_bars=200 is insufficient. Eval silently produces 0 decisions with no error when the warmup requirement is not met.","recommendation":"For any strategy using rvol_tod_N: compute required_bars = N × (1440/cadence_minutes) and ensure scenario duration exceeds this. Use volume_zscore_20 as a drop-in substitute — it only needs 20-bar warmup and fires on any 2σ volume anomaly.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"session 2026-06-07/08 Ollama strategy loop (V9b finding F18)","date":"2026-06-08"}],"tags":["xvision-filters","rvol-tod","warmup","eval","indicators"],"affectedFiles":["crates/xvision-filters/src/types.rs","crates/xvision-cli/src/commands/eval/mod.rs"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-06-08T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-06-08T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-serde-untagged-nested-enum-error-loss","type":"gotcha","fact":"serde(untagged) on filter DSL enums swallows targeted error messages. ConditionItem variants Leaf(Condition) and Group(ConditionGroup) both have custom Deserialize (OperandVisitor produces specific 'invalid indicator DSL token' messages). With #[serde(untagged)], any inner error becomes the generic 'data did not match any variant of untagged enum' — operators cannot diagnose filter parse failures.","recommendation":"For xvision-filters enums that wrap types with custom error reporting, use a custom visit_map Deserialize impl that peeks at keys (all/any → Group; anything else → Condition) and propagates original inner errors. Never use #[serde(untagged)] when inner Deserialize impls produce diagnostic-quality error messages you want to preserve.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"B-W1 implementation 2026-06-08 — B-W1 agent chose custom Deserialize over #[serde(untagged)]","date":"2026-06-08"}],"tags":["xvision-filters","serde","deserialization","error-messages","ConditionItem"],"affectedFiles":["crates/xvision-filters/src/types.rs"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-06-08T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-06-08T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-eval-agent-run-single-id","type":"gotcha","fact":"For eval/live runs the agent_runs row is seeded at the SAME id as the eval_runs row (ensure_agent_run_baseline in crates/xvision-engine/src/api/eval.rs), so agent_runs.id == eval_runs.id and GET /api/agent-runs/<eval_id> resolves. The frontend traceRunId = agent_run_id ?? eval_run.id fallback is INTENTIONAL, not a bug.","recommendation":"Do NOT add a separate agent_run_id field to RunSummary to fix trace linkage; the single-id pattern already provides it. The old agent-run-not-found View Trace error was a write race (async emit_run_started), fixed by the synchronous baseline seed + UPSERT.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"session","reference":"trace-obs WS-1","date":"2026-06-14"}],"tags":["observability","agent-runs","eval","trace"],"affectedFiles":["crates/xvision-engine/src/api/eval.rs","frontend/web/src/routes/eval-runs-detail.tsx"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-06-14T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-06-14T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"gotcha-coverage-gate-rust-only","type":"gotcha","fact":".coverage-thresholds.json enforcement is scripts/cargo tarpaulin --fail-under 100 — Rust-only, cargo-tarpaulin is not installed, 100% workspace coverage is infeasible, and it does not measure the frontend.","recommendation":"For frontend (TS/React) work units enforce 100% coverage on CHANGED code via vitest @vitest/coverage-v8 (check changed line ranges, not whole-file %, which is <100 from pre-existing untested code). Leave the Rust tarpaulin command intact for backend WUs. Working frontend gates: pnpm typecheck, pnpm test (no lint script).","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"human","reference":"trace-obs WS-1/WS-2 operator-approved","date":"2026-06-14"}],"tags":["testing","coverage","frontend","metaswarm","ci"],"affectedFiles":[".coverage-thresholds.json","frontend/web/**"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-06-14T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-06-14T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
